Learning Theory
Hypothesis Testing
1: What are the 5 steps:
// Step 1: State null and alternative hypothesis //
// Step 2: Select a level of significance //
// Step 3: Identify test statistic //
// Step 4: Formulate decision rule//
// Step 5: Take a sample, and arrive at a decision//

2A: Null Hypothesis (H0)
// State there is no difference between parameter and specific value //
2B: Alternative Hypothesis (H1)
// State there is an existence value between the parameter and specific value //

3: Type of test
// a) 1-tailed test: left-tailed and right-tailed //
//    - H0 should be rejected when the test value is in a critical region on one side of the mean //
// b) 2-tailed test //
//    - H0 should be rejected when the test value is in either of the 2 critical regions//

4: Level of significance
// Max probability of committing a type error //
// 0.10(10%), 0.05(5%), 0.01(1%) //

